Java specification for accessing, persisting, and managing data between Java objects and relational databases.
EntityManagerFactory is a key interface in the JPA responsible for creating and managing EntityManager instances, factory for EntityManager objects, allowing applications to obtain EntityManager instances configured for a specific persistence unit.
EntityManager is a key interface in JPA that manages the lifecycle of entities and provides methods for performing CRUD operations on entities.
In summary..we've many orm tools such as Hibernate,eclipselink,ibatis etc..
So..if we're familiar with hibernate and client wants us to work with other orm tool which isn't familiar for us.
In that use..JPA is useful by means of standardizing everything across all tools and onnly have modify some lines and configure xml file.
